text: Cantey is an unincorporated community in Kershaw County, in the U.S. state of South Carolina. ==History== The community was named after the local Cantey family, early settlers. A variant name is "Cantey Hill". A post office called Cantey was established in 1884, and remained in operation until 1921. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in South Carolina Category:Unincorporated communities in Kershaw County, South Carolina
title: Cantey, South Carolina
